<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="497">Note:</emphasis>
Hauke (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="497">Nova Hedwigia</emphasis>
13: 106. 1966) indicated 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="497">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Löfling">Loefling</normalizedToken>
713
</emphasis>
(1241.4 LINN) as &quot;a type for the name&quot;, but he believed that it was a post-1753 addition to the herbarium, and evidently treated it as a 
<typeStatus>neotype</typeStatus>
. As original material is in existence, designation of a 
<typeStatus>neotype</typeStatus>
is contrary to Art. 9.11, and Jonsell &amp; Jarvis therefore rejected 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Hauke’s">Hauke's</normalizedToken>
choice in favour of a Clayton collection.
</paragraph>
